The paper deals with the construction of spanners in high dimensional normed spaces, which is a topic in computational geometry and data structures (cs.CG and cs.DS). The use of stochastic decompositions to obtain light spanners is a technique from probability theory and information theory (cs.IT), and the analysis of the sparsity and lightness of the spanners involves mathematical optimization and numerical analysis (cs.MS and cs.NA).
